5. Why simple ratios dominate

Systems naturally drift toward stable configurations.

Simple ratios are stable because:
	•	they repeat predictably
	•	energy exchanges stay consistent
	•	small disturbances cancel out

That’s why you see them in:
	•	atoms
	•	planetary systems
	•	musical scales
	•	biological rhythms

